text: ICYMI: I spoke on the floor yesterday about my push for a long-term solution to #FixTheTrustFund this summer: http://t.co/CGiCslsR60
name: Tom Carper

text: An amazing coalition of stakeholders support a long-term transportation bill, and their message to us is the same: #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: The 18.3 cent federal gas tax we set in 1993 is now worth about a dime. The 24.3 cent diesel tax is worth about 15 cents. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: It’s like taking a road trip and filling your car with gas one gallon at a time. It’s no way to run a country. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: The Framers of the Constitution had the sense say it is the role of the government to provide transportation systems. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: You have to plan, fund, contract, and get permits for transportation projects. It takes years. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: Short-term extensions undermine governors and mayors around the country, preventing investments in critical projects. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: Since 2008, we haven’t had a transportation bill lasting more than 2 years. Some have lasted as little as a few days. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: Infrastructure is how we move people and goods, and it’s the key to an efficient and growing economy. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: As a former governor, I've seen the impact that roads, bridges, and transit systems have on economic growth and success. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper

text: Abraham Lincoln once said that it is the role of government to do for the people what they cannot do for themselves. #FixTheTrustFund
name: Tom Carper
